{
  "text": "In this way, the parallel influence of both the Coulomb interaction and SOC is considered [CITATION_1] . To solve the resulting equation, we use the analogy of the numerical method used in [CITATION_2] -this analogy is presented in [CITATION_3] . From the calculated results, LDOS is calculated using Eq. (33) again. The graphs of LDOS based on the found solution are sketched in Figure 13 for the same modes and numbers of the defects as in Figure 12 , i.e. \u22121 \u2264 j \u2264 3. In spite of our expectations, this time the behaviour of the found result is the same for arbitrary number of the defects, i.e. the appearance and the uniqueness of the peak in the case of 3 defects is distorted.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "119244167",
